Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with governors and mayors/county executives to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The call included elected officials such as Governor Steve Beshear, Governor Mitch Daniels, Governor Bill Ritter, Governor Michael Rounds, Governor Ted Strickland, Mayor Greg Ballard, Mayor David Cicilline, Mayor Frank Cownie, Mayor Frank Jackson, Mayor Pat McCrory, Mayor Mike Ragsdale, and Chair of County Commission, Judge Glen Whitley. The purpose of the call was to discuss the progress and challenges of implementing the Recovery Act.